        <category>service-catalog</category>
        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Service catalog record producers</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p"><span class="ph">A record producer is a specific type of catalog item that allows          end users to create task-based records, such as incident records, from the service          catalog.</span></p>  <p class="p">Use record producers to provide a better end-user experience instead of        using the regular task-based form for creating records. The look and feel of a record        producer is similar to that of a catalog item. But the record producer generates a task        record such as incident, instead of a requested item. </p>  <div class="note note"><span class="notetitle">Note:</span>         <ul class="ul" id="sc_cat_item_producer_list-normal__d25211e96"><li class="li">Use a record producer to create task-based records only.</li><li class="li">To ensure that standard service catalog processes are followed, such as initiating            workflows as expected, do not create requested item records from record producers.            Instead, create requested item using catalog items.</li></ul>      </div> </div> <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Record_Producer&amp;version&#61;jakarta" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Record producer</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
